#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:5
#: c59fd51e2d254e3d9f2663a7b8be756d
msgid "Chats vs Channels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:7
#: dc01b94a66164f83b4fc92e90f8fd507
msgid ""
"Telegram's raw API can get very confusing sometimes, in particular when "
"it comes to talking about \"chats\", \"channels\", \"groups\", "
"\"megagroups\", and all those concepts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:11
#: 7f1088a99fdf4cd580852c9ca275e596
msgid "This section will try to explain what each of these concepts are."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:15
#: 5fbb876ef1a8482d93ccc4ece4732cf2
msgid "Chats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:17
#: a554dfb2dba645d0ad98063ef1c3bd05
msgid ""
"A ``Chat`` can be used to talk about either the common \"subclass\" that "
"both chats and channels share, or the concrete :tl:`Chat` type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:20
#: ef9a7a5bf1434e74bc446c946204c949
msgid ""
"Technically, both :tl:`Chat` and :tl:`Channel` are a form of the `Chat "
"type`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:22
#: 93703cd5bd684e2f8571ce921f8818ff
msgid ""
"**Most of the time**, the term :tl:`Chat` is used to talk about *small "
"group chats*. When you create a group through an official application, "
"this is the type that you get. Official applications refer to these as "
"\"Group\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:26
#: f4348153c638430dbf91502eaf3141e4
msgid ""
"Both the bot API and Telethon will add a minus sign (negate) the real "
"chat ID so that you can tell at a glance, with just a number, the entity "
"type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:29
#: 2d11a0b1bb7a470b93ca8fd0a6a0d23f
msgid ""
"For example, if you create a chat with :tl:`CreateChatRequest`, the real "
"chat ID might be something like `123`. If you try printing it from a "
"`message.chat_id` you will see `-123`. This ID helps Telethon know you're"
" talking about a :tl:`Chat`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:36
#: b3f9861a0d8b440794f864ef7c55764b
msgid "Channels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:38
#: cc5d9f4739764a9fa385aca3911c8daa
msgid ""
"Official applications create a *broadcast* channel when you create a new "
"channel (used to broadcast messages, only administrators can post "
"messages)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:41
#: 8ce005d8c3e14d31bfd4ff71fc14693e
msgid ""
"Official applications implicitly *migrate* an *existing* :tl:`Chat` to a "
"*megagroup* :tl:`Channel` when you perform certain actions (exceed user "
"limit, add a public username, set certain permissions, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:45
#: 79126e3c8d4444869df44db1069122a7
msgid ""
"A ``Channel`` can be created directly with :tl:`CreateChannelRequest`, as"
" either a ``megagroup`` or ``broadcast``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:48
#: 9c493dffa48d4792a3c8da5f9000e247
msgid ""
"Official applications use the term \"channel\" **only** for broadcast "
"channels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:50
#: 6bc4aa2b9dd841cc8edbddc47fecf02b
msgid ""
"The API refers to the different types of :tl:`Channel` with certain "
"attributes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:52
#: 86246b95da144ad19ed6bb3af2ab9b4b
msgid ""
"A **broadcast channel** is a :tl:`Channel` with the ``channel.broadcast``"
" attribute set to `True`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:55
#: cd7affc0d4c2439a85139a33d5b61bd5
msgid ""
"A **megagroup channel** is a :tl:`Channel` with the ``channel.megagroup``"
" attribute set to `True`. Official applications refer to this as "
"\"supergroup\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:58
#: 3897795a356f402b87633c6f13ac4d05
msgid ""
"A **gigagroup channel** is a :tl:`Channel` with the ``channel.gigagroup``"
" attribute set to `True`. Official applications refer to this as "
"\"broadcast groups\", and is used when a megagroup becomes very large and"
" administrators want to transform it into something where only they can "
"post messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:64
#: 9f59bd1e95e2420fbe5bdb2934bb8c1e
msgid ""
"Both the bot API and Telethon will \"concatenate\" ``-100`` to the real "
"chat ID so that you can tell at a glance, with just a number, the entity "
"type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/chats-vs-channels.rst:67
#: b34f5f367c8043c4aaeeac945ee5281d
msgid ""
"For example, if you create a new broadcast channel, the real channel ID "
"might be something like `456`. If you try printing it from a "
"`message.chat_id` you will see `-1000000000456`. This ID helps Telethon "
"know you're talking about a :tl:`Channel`."
msgstr ""

